  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To compare the calculated biventricular ejection fraction from cadmium-zinc-telluride (CZT)
      single photon emission computed tomography (SPECT) with planar equilibrium radionuclide
      angiography (ERNA), first-pass radionuclide ventriculography (FP-RNV) and echocardiogram.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate the feasibility of using CZT SPECT as an &quot;all-in-one&quot; technique to provide
      information on both left ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF) and right ventricular ejection
      fraction (RVEF) derived from a single examination and compare with the values from
      traditional planar ERNA, FP-RNV and echocardiography.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
